12/05/2004
ZADAR, Croatia -- Prime Minister Ivo Sanader urged on Tuesday (11 May) that the public leave the war behind, as the "country's future lies in reconciliation and tolerance".
He added the government would do its best to ensure a "dignified life" for every citizen.
Sanader spoke during a visit to the central Adriatic town of Zadar.
Accompanying him was Bulgarian Foreign Minister Solomon Passy, the current chairman of the OSCE.
They inspected the progress of efforts to repair war-damaged houses and other aspects of the refugee return process.
(HINA, Vecernji List, AFP - 11/05/04)
